Bazel-sandbox fixes for the anki_proto build script (#278 cutover). Applied by
the crate annotation in MODULE.bazel — plain cargo builds use the unpatched
checkout, so the local flow and the pip wheel are untouched.

Three sandbox realities:
* write_python_interface / write_ts_interface write generated interface files
  INTO THE SOURCE CHECKOUT (`../../out/...`), read-only under Bazel. Shrike
  consumes neither (the Rust service layer only) — dropped.
* The source repo's proto/ tree and protoc itself are not available in the
  build-script sandbox (crate_universe materializes only the crate package).
  With DESCRIPTORS_BIN set (the annotation points it at the checked-in pinned
  descriptor set, //native/third_party/anki), codegen runs via prost's
  compile_fds — generate-from-descriptors, no protoc, no proto files.
* descriptors_path() defaults to `OUT_DIR/../../anki_descriptors.bin`,
  cargo's shared target layout, which doesn't exist across Bazel sandboxes —
  the build script keeps its descriptor copy inside its own OUT_DIR.

--- a/build.rs
+++ b/build.rs
@@ -5,17 +5,15 @@
 pub mod rust;
 pub mod typescript;
 
-use anki_proto_gen::descriptors_path;
 use anki_proto_gen::get_services;
 use anyhow::Result;
 
 fn main() -> Result<()> {
-    let descriptors_path = descriptors_path();
+    let descriptors_path = std::path::PathBuf::from(std::env::var("OUT_DIR").unwrap())
+        .join("anki_descriptors.bin");
 
     let pool = rust::write_rust_protos(descriptors_path)?;
-    let (_, services) = get_services(&pool);
-    python::write_python_interface(&services)?;
-    typescript::write_ts_interface(&services)?;
+    let _ = get_services(&pool);
 
     Ok(())
 }
